  09 Jul 2006; Diego Pettenò <flameeyes@gentoo.org>
  libvisual-plugins-0.2.0.ebuild, libvisual-plugins-0.4.0.ebuild:
  Remove xorg-server fake depend, was an artefact produced by the first dep
  checking scripts.

*libvisual-plugins-0.4.0 (28 May 2006)

  28 May 2006; Diego Pettenò <flameeyes@gentoo.org>
  -libvisual-plugins-0.1.6.ebuild, -libvisual-plugins-0.1.7.ebuild,
  libvisual-plugins-0.2.0.ebuild, +libvisual-plugins-0.4.0.ebuild:
  Version bump to latest version upstream, slotted as this is incompatible
  with 0.2 series. Thanks to Alejandro Nova and Gleb Litvjak in bug #131733.

  20 Feb 2006; Gustavo Zacarias <gustavoz@gentoo.org>
  libvisual-plugins-0.2.0.ebuild:
  Stable on sparc

  11 Feb 2006; Markus Rothe <corsair@gentoo.org>
  libvisual-plugins-0.2.0.ebuild:
  Stable on ppc64

  07 Jan 2006; <chainsaw@gentoo.org>
  +files/libvisual-plugins-0.2.0-gcc4.patch, libvisual-plugins-0.2.0.ebuild:
  GCC4 compatability patch from upstream, closes bug #118050. Thanks to Mark
  Loeser <halcy0n@gentoo.org>.

  23 Dec 2005; Markus Rothe <corsair@gentoo.org>
  libvisual-plugins-0.2.0.ebuild:
  Added ~ppc64

  10 Dec 2005; Diego Pettenò <flameeyes@gentoo.org>
  +files/libvisual-plugins-0.2.0-mkdirhier.patch,
  libvisual-plugins-0.2.0.ebuild:
  Added patch from bug #112706 to actually make it compile on modular xorg.

  10 Dec 2005; Diego Pettenò <flameeyes@gentoo.org>
  libvisual-plugins-0.2.0.ebuild:
  Made modular xorg friendly.

  17 Jun 2005; Joseph Jezak <josejx@gentoo.org>
  libvisual-plugins-0.2.0.ebuild:
  Marked ppc stable.

  14 May 2005; Heinrich Wendel <lanius@gentoo.org>
  libvisual-plugins-0.2.0.ebuild:
  stable on amd64 and x86

